        <main>
          <h1 class="title">Postgraduate Study</h1>
          <nav class="primary-nav">
            <span class="nav-title">Software Engineering<i class="nav-toggle"></i></span>
            <div class="nav-links">
              <a href="/research/groupings/software_engineering/component-based" class="nav-link">Component Based</a>
              <a href="/research/groupings/software_engineering/cloud-computing" class="nav-link">Cloud Computing</a>
              <a href="/research/groupings/software_engineering/people" class="nav-link">People</a>
              <a href="/research/groupings/software_engineering/postgraduate-study" class="nav-link">Postgraduate Study</a>
            </div>
          </nav>
          <p>The School of Computer Science provides specialist teaching and conducts research in software engineering. We are proud to deliver outstanding postgraduate education that offers varied and exciting career opportunities around the world. We offer a taught MEng course in Software Engineering and supervision for postgraduate research.</p>

<h2>MEng Software Engineering</h2>

<p>The MEng in Software Engineering is a four-year full-time undergraduate Masters degree course based on the three year BEng Computer Science with Software Engineering degree. For full details please refer to the <a href="/admissions/undergraduate/degrees/se">MEng Software Engineering page</a>. The School also offers taught postgraduate programmes in other disciplies.</p>

<h2>Postgraduate research (PhD)</h2>

<p>The School boasts a tradition of academic excellence and produces internationally recognised research. The PhD programme is typically three years of individual research on a topic agreed between the student and supervisor. Applicants should be highly motivated and have an outstanding academic record. Further details can be found on the <a href="/admissions/postgraduate/research/">postgraduate research page</a>.</p>

